# Environment setup — see env.config.example and env.secret.example
#
# 1. cp env.config.example env.config
# 2. cp env.secret.example env.secret
# 3. Fill in values
# 4. npm run env:compose   → generates .env
# 5. npm run dev
#
# Sync to Vercel production: npm run sync:vercel (see AGENTS.md)
# Playground vars (PLAYGROUND_*) are local dev only — never sync to production.
